## Why firewall-drop Does Not Apply to DCSync

This is an important architectural distinction.

firewall-drop blocks the SOURCE IP of the alert.
For DCSync, Event 4662 is logged on DC01 (10.0.0.10),
not on the attacker machine (10.0.0.99).

Blocking DC01 would isolate the Domain Controller itself,
which is catastrophically worse than the attack.

**This is correct behavior — not a limitation.**

### Correct Production Response for DCSync
| Priority | Action | Command |
|---|---|---|
| IMMEDIATE | Disable compromised account | `Disable-ADAccount -Identity svc-mssql` |
| IMMEDIATE | Revoke DCSync DACL rights | `dacledit.py -action remove` |
| URGENT | Rotate krbtgt password (×2) | `Set-ADAccountPassword -Identity krbtgt` |
| URGENT | Alert SOC team | Wazuh notification |
| FOLLOW-UP | Map full blast radius | BloodHound re-enumeration |
| FOLLOW-UP | Reset all exposed account passwords | Active Directory |
```powershell
# Immediate containment on DC01
Disable-ADAccount -Identity svc-mssql
Write-Host "svc-mssql disabled" -ForegroundColor Red

# Rotate krbtgt — must be done TWICE, 10 hours apart
Set-ADAccountPassword -Identity krbtgt `
  -NewPassword (ConvertTo-SecureString "NewSecureP@ss2026!" -AsPlainText -Force) `
  -Reset
```

## Remediation
| Action | Priority | Impact |
|---|---|---|
| Audit and remove WriteDACL from service accounts | CRITICAL | Prevents ACL abuse |
| Implement tiered administration model | CRITICAL | Limits blast radius |
| Regular BloodHound ACL audits | HIGH | Early misconfiguration detection |
| Enable Protected Users Security Group | HIGH | Limits credential exposure |
| Monitor Event ID 4662 with replication GUIDs | HIGH | Early DCSync detection |
| Rotate krbtgt password regularly | HIGH | Limits Golden Ticket attacks |
| Remove unnecessary Extended Rights from all accounts | MEDIUM | Reduces attack surface |